      "date": "2019-12-09 17:41:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nconfigure:30423: checking if ZFS has multihost protection\nconfigure:30446: gcc -c -g -O2 -I/usr/include/libspl -I /usr/include/libzfs -Werror -I/usr/src/lustre-2.13.50/libcfs/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.13.50/lnet/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.13.50/lnet/include/uapi -I/usr/src/lustre-2.13.50/lustre/include -I/usr/src/lustre-2.13.50/lustre/include/uapi conftest.c >&5\nIn file included from /usr/include/libzfs/sys/zfs_context.h:103,\n         from /usr/include/libzfs/sys/spa.h:37,\n         from conftest.c:225:\n/usr/include/libspl/sys/sysmacros.h:101: error: \"_NOTE\" redefined [-Werror]\n 101 | #define _NOTE(x)\n   | \nIn file included from /usr/include/libzfs/sys/zfs_context.h:100,\n         from /usr/include/libzfs/sys/spa.h:37,\n         from conftest.c:225:\n/usr/include/libzfs/sys/note.h:47: note: this is the location of the previous definition\n  47 | #define _NOTE(s)\n   | \ncc1: all warnings being treated as errors\nconfigure:30446: $? = 1\nif I enable multihost it works no problem",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
